![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

`sem_getvalue` is not supported on macOS (it returns `-1` and sets `errno` to `ENOSYS`). Since this test file is compiled for both Linux and macOS, these assertions will fail on macOS. Consider wrapping these checks in `#ifdef __linux__` or using an alternative way to verify the initial state if macOS support is required for this test.

```suggestion
#ifdef __linux__
  int obj_val = -1, hdr_val = -1;
  ASSERT_EQ(0, sem_getvalue(sem.object_sem, &obj_val));
  ASSERT_EQ(0, sem_getvalue(sem.header_sem, &hdr_val));
  ASSERT_EQ(1, obj_val) << "object_sem should be initialized to 1";
  ASSERT_EQ(1, hdr_val) << "header_sem should be initialized to 1";
#endif
```

